<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS NORTHRIDGE SIGNS BEVERLY HILLS CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peter Micelli, a 6-foot-8 center from Beverly Hills High, signed a national 
letter of intent Thursday to play basketball for Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Micelli, who averaged 24 points and 14 rebounds a game, was the Bay League's 
Most Valuable Player last season. He is the seventh player to sign with 
Northridge, which will move from the NCAA Division II to Division I level next 
season. Five junior college players signed Wednesday; a high school player 
signed in November. 
</P>
