<HEADLINE>
<P>
8 OFFICERS WOUNDED IN ALGERIAN INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ALGIERS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eight police officers were wounded in nightlong clashes with youths outside a 
theater in the Algerian capital that resulted in 19 arrests, police said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The Algerian news agency APS quoted a police statement saying the incident 
started when Muslim fundamentalists tried to stop a concert taking place across 
the street from a mosque during the holy month of Ramadan. 
</P>
