<TEXT>
<P>
SEC Probing First Chicago Statements: The Securities and Exchange Commission 
has begun an inquiry into allegations that First Chicago Corp. leaked certain 
sensitive information to securities analysts in advance of a public 
announcement projecting lower first-quarter earnings. 
</P>
<P>
Some analysts said the probe has the potential to change the landscape of their 
profession. The SEC declined to comment on the inquiry. The analysts worry that 
allegations that First Chicago improperly disclosed an impending increase in 
non-performing loans could freeze the information flow that is their lifeblood. 
They said what they learned from First Chicago was the routine information that 
their profession relies on. 
</P>
</TEXT>
