BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paramount Modifies Rental Fees: Paramount Pictures, which last year provoked a 
congressional investigation after changing the film rental fees it charges to 
discount movie theaters, said it has modified the fees. Paramount said it will 
now charge theaters a percentage of a film's box office gross four months after 
a movie is released, instead of five months after the release. 
</P>
<P>
In the first four months after release, Paramount will continue to charge 
theaters a minimum per person payment of $1.05 for adults and 75 cents for 
children, or 35% of the box office gross, whichever is higher. Paramount last 
May instituted the minimum per-capita payment, prompting an outcry from 
discount movie theaters, which show second-run films for an admission price as 
low as $1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
