</P>
<P>
NEW JERSEY; 
</P>
<P>
VIOLENCE FLARES AFTER OFFICER SHOOTS YOUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Teen-agers, mostly blacks, roamed the streets of Teaneck, N.J., after a night 
of smashing windows and overturning cars following the fatal shooting of a 
black teen-ager by a white policeman. 
</P>
<P>
The Wednesday night street violence broke out after a peaceful candlelight 
protest over Tuesday's death of 15-year-old Phillip Pannell of River Edge. City 
Police Chief Bryan Burke said six police cars were destroyed during the 
violence and store windows were shattered. Witnesses said police pushed the 
protesters into the parking lot of police headquarters and some women and 
children were trampled. The crowd retaliated by turning over cars and throwing 
rocks and other debris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
