<P>
STORE OWNER HELD UP BY GUNMAN ON HIS WAY TO BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The owner of a Garden Grove convenience store, who was about to deposit his 
store's receipts, was robbed Thursday of $7,000 in the parking lot of a bank, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Surjit Singh Bajwa, 31, of Westminster was approached by a man armed with a 
handgun about 2:20 p.m. as Bajwa stepped from his car in the parking lot of 
Bank of America, 6951 Westminster Blvd., Sgt. Bill Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
Bajwa, who operates a 7-Eleven store, handed the robber the money and was not 
harmed, Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
The bandit was described as white with brown hair, 20 to 25 years old, about 
six feet tall and weighing 180 pounds. He was wearing a light-colored shirt and 
jeans. He was seen fleeing in an older-model orange Datsun station wagon, the 
sergeant said. 
</P>
