<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. HALL OF FAME GIVES TO YOUTH TEAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Sports Hall of Fame gave more than $60,000 to 11 Little 
League and Bobby Sox leagues in Orange County Thursday night at Anaheim 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
The annual Field of Dreams grants were distributed among the oldest and largest 
leagues to help the groups make improvements to baseball and softball fields in 
parks in both Orange and Riverside counties. 
</P>
<P>
"We want to take care of our youth," said Bobby McDonald, president of the Hall 
of Fame. 
</P>
<P>
Funds came from the Major League All-Star Game, held last July at Anaheim 
Stadium, and other Hall of Fame fund-raising events. 
</P>
<P>
In Anaheim, Loara Little League and East Anaheim National Little League 
received funds, and Valley Little League of Santa Ana, South Sunrise Little 
League of Orange, Central Orange Bobby Sox, Fountain Valley Little League North 
and South, and Westminster Little League were also among the recipients. 
</P>
<P>
The organization also made a separate grant of $10,000 to the Anaheim Parks, 
Recreation and Community Services Department. LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
