<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RANCHO SANTIAGO REACHES SEMIFINAL AT CHANNEL COAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rancho Santiago had 19 hits to easily defeat Cosumnes River College of 
Sacramento, 10-3, in a quarterfinal game of the Channel Coast baseball 
tournament at Moorpark College in Simi Valley Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff White and Sean Sterling each had three hits and scored twice to lead 
Rancho Santiago (26-5). 
</P>
<P>
Matt Lackie (9-2) pitched six innings to earn the win. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 9, Long Beach 7 -- The Hornets (18-11) scored seven runs in the third 
inning to take a 7-4 lead and went on to win at Fullerton. Jim Short and Kevin 
Monson both had two-run doubles in the inning. Jeff Manship had a two-run 
single that broke a 4-4 tie. 
</P>
<P>
In a semifinal of the Hancock baseball tournament in Santa Maria: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 8, College of the Canyons 7 -- Freshman Kevin Cook hit a two-run 
pinch-hit home run to tie the game at 6-6 in the fifth inning. In the sixth, 
Doug McConnathy and Tom Tuppe hit back-to-back doubles and Tuppe later scored 
on a sacrifice fly by Tom Acuna for what proved to be the winning run. College 
of the Canyons scored one in the ninth but Kenny Kendrena stranded three 
runners to earn his second save. Aaron Charlton (3-2) got the win for Cypress 
(19-14). 
</P>
