<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOT TOPICS: HIGH LIFE A WEEKLY FORUM FOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS; 
</P>
<P>
FRIDAY THE 13TH REARS ITS STAR-CROSSED HEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If ever there was a day to stay in bed and pull the covers up over your head . 
. . today's that day. 
</P>
<P>
It's Friday the 13th, and if anything bad is going to happen to you, legend 
says it will happen today. 
</P>
<P>
Hot Topics wonders, "What are you superstitious about?" 
</P>
<P>
"Stepping on a crack, because as a child I was always told, 'If you step on a 
crack, you'll break your mother's back.' " 
</P>
<P>
Laura Greco, 15, 
</P>
<P>
freshman, Santa Margarita 
</P>
