<P>
Wild Art 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041390-0171 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 204181 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 13, 1990, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 1; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
65 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dave Lesher and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TONIGHT: They appeared in a handful of '60s beach movies but never toured 
together during their heyday as clean-cut teen idols. 
</P>
<P>
Now Frankie and Annette (Avalon and Funicello) kick off a 35-city tour at 
Knott's Berry Farm (F24). Times: 5 and 8 p.m. today and Saturday. Tickets: 
included with park admission of $15 to $21. Information: (714) 827-1776. Dave 
Lesher and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</TEXT>
