<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE; 
</P>
<P>
ON THE MOVE: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Another company goes south: O'Connell Landscape Maintenance, in Santa Ana since 
1971, is moving to Rancho Santa Margarita. 
</P>
<P>
More companies are following their employees into the relatively undeveloped 
southern portion of the county, where most of the new housing is being built. 
</P>
<P>
That trend has meant a boom for industrial parks south of the Costa Mesa 
Freeway too. 
</P>
<P>
The company bought a 1.3-acre site and will spend $1.3 million to build a 
12,600-square-foot building. In O'Connell's case, picking a new address in the 
big planned community was attractive because most of its customers are in South 
County. Still, development in South County has exceeded roads' capacities to 
handle the traffic. However, new roads are being planned or built. 
</P>
</TEXT>
