<P>
1 KILLED, 6 HURT IN COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was killed and six other people, including four children, were injured 
when a car ran a stop sign and hit another car broadside at an intersection 
near Palmdale, the California Highway Patrol reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The CHP said a 58-year-old Littlerock man died about 8:20 p.m. Thursday after 
the car he was driving northbound on 110th Street went through a stop sign at 
Palmdale Boulevard and crashed into the side of a westbound car carrying five 
people. 
</P>
<P>
The identity of the dead man was not released pending notification of his 
family. A passenger in his car, Michael Jackson, 35, of Littlerock, suffered 
major injuries. 
</P>
<P>
In the other car, the driver, Steven Schroeder, 33, of Murrieta, Calif., also 
suffered major injuries. His passengers, Laura Schroeder, 31, Kimberly 
Schroeder, 1, Jamie Henderson, 10, and Kevin Henderson, 9, suffered minor to 
moderate injuries. All of the injured were treated at hospitals in the Antelope 
Valley, Officer Miguel Siordia said. 
</P>
<P>
Siordia said it is unclear why the driver did not stop his car at the 
intersection. Alcohol did not appear to play a part in the accident, he said. 
Both Palmdale Boulevard and 110th Street are major thoroughfares in the area 
southeast of Palmdale, Siordia said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
