<P>
Essegian -- Former Dodger Chuck Essegian was not the first man to play in Rose 
Bowl game and World Series, as was reported in Thursday's editions. 
California's Jackie Jensen played in the 1949 Rose Bowl game against 
Northwestern and also appeared in the World Series for the New York Yankees in 
1950. 
